description:
1. Choose notification platform: Slack (create webhook in Slack workspace > Apps > Incoming Webhooks) OR Discord (Server Settings > Integrations > Webhooks). 2. Add webhook URL to `.env.local`: `NOTIFICATION_WEBHOOK_URL=[webhook-url]` and Vercel env vars. 3. Update `/Users/michaelguo/arcticruff/src/app/api/waitlist/route.ts`: after successful Supabase insert, send notification: `try { await fetch(process.env.NOTIFICATION_WEBHOOK_URL!, { method: 'POST', headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }, body: JSON.stringify({ text: \`🎉 New waitlist signup!
Name: \${name}
Email: \${email}
Model: \${jacket_model}
Fur: \${fur_color_preference}
Time: \${new Date().toISOString()}\` }) }); } catch (err) { console.error('Webhook notification failed:', err); }` Webhook failure should be logged but never block signup success response.
